SIMPLE: revie
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Revie
<hw>Re*vie"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To vie
with, or rival, in return.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Card Playing)</fld> <def>To meet a wager on, as on
the taking of a trick, with a higher wager.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revie</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Revie
<hw>Re*vie"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To exceed an
adversary's wager in card playing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make a retort; to bandy words.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Review</ent>⟦br⟧
